-- Reports of police searches weigh on UBI shares-traders
-- 
-- Wed May 14, 2014 04:41AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, May 14 (Reuters) - Shares in UBI Banca <UBI.MI> fell 3.4 percent on Wednesday, underperforming a 1 percent fall in Italy's banking index <.FTIT8300>, following reports of tax police searches at the bank's headquarters in the northern Italian town of Bergamo.

Two traders and an analyst said the fall was linked to the news of the searches, which a tax police source says are part of an inquiry into possible obstruction to regulators and fraud. [nL6N0O027V] Shares in UBI rose at open on Wednesday, following release of first-quarter results.